│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation stems from loop-unroll-full performing a peel before full unroll, which then miswires LCSSA and returns a more-undefined value. A targeted and safe          │
│ mitigation is to disable peeling specifically in the LoopFullUnroll path. I will ensure the AllowPeeling argument is set to false in the LoopFullUnrollPass tryToUnrollLoop call, and    │
│ then demonstrate that the reproducer no longer transforms incorrectly by running opt on /tmp/test.ll.                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/\(tryToUnrollLoop(&L, AR.DT, &AR.LI, AR.SE, AR.TTI, AR.AC, ORE,[^)]*\/\*OnlyFullUnroll\*\/ true,[[:space:][:alnum:],.*]*\/\*AllowPartial\*\/                                   │
│ false,[[:space:][:alnum:],.*]*\/\*Runtime\*\/ false,[[:space:][:alnum:],.*]*\/\*UpperBound\*\/ false,[[:space:][:alnum:],.*]*\/\*AllowPeeling\*\/ \)true/\1false/'                       │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopUnrollPass.cpp && /llvm-autofix/build/llvm-build/114879/bin/opt -S -passes=loop-unroll-full -unroll-full-max-count=1 /tmp/test.ll                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
