│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation in the reproducer stems from peeling in the LoopFullUnroll pipeline, which miswires LCSSA and yields a more-undefined result. I implemented a targeted fix   │
│ by disabling peeling specifically when OnlyFullUnroll is true (setting AllowPeeling to false in LoopFullUnrollPass’s tryToUnrollLoop call). This avoids the problematic sequence while   │
│ leaving other unroll paths unchanged. The reproducer now no longer transforms incorrectly under loop-unroll-full with max count 1. I will now submit the patch for validation.           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
